article.headline: Stetson 62, Savannah State 53
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Stetson rally to beat Savannah State 62-53 Wednesday night. Stetson (8-17) led 28-25 at halftime and extended the lead to 30-25 on a layup by Gabe McMillen in the opening seconds of the second half. But Savannah State (2-25) held Stetson scoreless for the next six minutes and took a 31-30 lead on a jumper by Joseph Flegler with 13:46 to play. Savannah State led by as many as six points, the last time 42-36 with 6:49 left on two free throws by Michael Bennett. Back-to-back 3-pointers by Eric Diaz and McMillen gave Stetson the lead for good at 46-44 with 3:12 to play. Gordon's jumper extended the lead to 48-44 and the Hatters gradually pulled away after that. Javon Randolph led Savannah State with 15 points.
